12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 4503, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 4503. A. As used in the Oklahoma Remote Quality Jobs
16 Incentive Act:
17 1. "Basic industry" means an establishment that attracts remote
18 workers to the state whose purpose is to increase the state's
19 population and who may receive rebates on the remote workers
20 provided that the remote workers meet the wage and health insurance
21 requirements in state and provide evidence of such to the proxy
22 establishment;
23 2. "New direct job" shall include full-time-equivalent
24 employment in this state of remote workers who are employed by an
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2746 Page 1

1 esta blishment other than the proxy establishment which has qualified
2 to receive incentive payments for attracting remote workers to the
3 state. Such jobs held by remote workers did not exist in this state
4 prior to the date of approval by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
5 of the application of the proxy establishment. A job shall be
6 deemed to exist in this state prior to approval of an application if
7 the activities and functions for which the particular job exists
8 have been ongoing at any time within six (6) months prior to such
9 approval;
10 3. "Proxy establishment" means:
11 a. a public trust which:
12 (1) is organized and existing under Section 176 of
13 Title 60 of the Oklahoma Statutes for the benefit
14 of a geographic area which includes a city or
15 county or some combination thereof, and
16 (2) benefits a geographic area where new direct jobs
17 which meet the requirements of the Oklahoma
18 Remote Quality Jobs Incentive Act are created by
19 an establishment, other than the proxy
20 establishment, or
21 b. an establishment which facilitates the attraction of
22 remote workers to the State of Oklahoma;
23 4. "Remote worker" refers to a work flexibility arrangement
24 under which an employee performs the duties and responsibilities of
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2746 Page 2

1 such employee's position, and other authorized activities, from an
2 approved work site other than the location from which the employee
3 would otherwise work, which shall not be located within the physical
4 boundaries of the State of Oklahoma. The remote worker should not
5 have lived in the State of Oklahoma in the previous twelve (12)
6 months;
7 5. "Estimated direct state benefits" means the tax revenues
8 projected by the Department to accrue to the state as a result of
9 new direct jobs;
10 6. "Estimated direct state costs" means the costs projected by
11 the Department to accrue to the state as a result of new direct
12 jobs. Such costs shall include, but not be limited to:
13 a. the costs of education of new state resident children,
14 b. the costs of public health, public safety and
15 transportation services to be provided to new state
16 residents,
17 c. the costs of other state services to be provided to
18 new state residents, and
19 d. the costs of other state services;
20 7. "Estimated net direct state benefits" means the estimated
21 direct state benefits less the estimated direct state costs; and
22 8. "Net benefit rate" means the estimated net direct state
23 benefits computed as a percentage of gross payroll, and shall not
24 exceed five percent (5%).
