1 B. A proxy establishment shall be required to obtain from
2 remote workers proof of basic health benefits plans for the
3 individuals it includes in an application. The proxy establishment
4 shall submit the information to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce
5 and shall ensure that the basic health benefits plans consist of the
6 following elements or elements substantially equivalent thereto:
7 1. Not more than fifty percent (50%) of the premium shall be
8 paid by the employee;
9 2. Coverage for basic hospital care;
10 3. Coverage for physician care;
11 4. Coverage for mental health care;
12 5. Coverage for substance abuse treatment;
13 6. Coverage for prescription drugs; and
14 7. Coverage for prenatal care.
15 provide coverage where not more than fifty percent (50%) of the
16 premium shall be paid by the employee; however, services provided by
17 an Employee Assistance Plan (EAP) are not sufficient to meet this
18 definition.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
